        Streamwalker says gently — "We've reviewed your documentation — dietary requirements, rest needs, human specifications. We're prepared."

        ¶

        This is it—the handoff, the goodbye. I find myself not ready.

        I ask — "So we just… transfer here?"

        Leafwhisper says, leaves rustling with forced cheerfulness — "Standard protocol! We'll document the successful Territory One crossing, confirm your condition, transfer guide responsibility to Streamwalker and Brightbloom, and then Rootwalker and I head back home! Very straightforward process—"

        Rootwalker agrees quietly — "Very."

        Scout bounces between me and the new guides, investigating, assessing.

        Brightbloom says — "Your Scout companion is welcome to continue, of course. We've guided sphere-types before. Lovely travelers!"

        Scout bounces approval and returns to my side.

        Streamwalker asks me directly — "How are you feeling? Ready to continue? The terrain changes significantly—more water, softer ground, different navigation challenges."

        I say — "I'm ready. I think."

        Leafwhisper's leaves shimmer. Leafwhisper says — "You absolutely are! Three days of excellent adaptation, you'll do wonderfully in Territory Two—"

        I say — "Thanks. For everything — the information, the patience, the…" I gesture vaguely. "All of it."

        Leafwhisper rustles — "Our pleasure! Truly! First human traveler — absolutely fascinating experience, learning so much about cross-species coordination and adaptive requirements—"

        Rootwalker moves closer and says — "Good traveler. Safe journey."

        Two words. Maximum sentiment from minimum speech.

        My throat feels tight.

        I say — "You too. Both of you. Thank you for… being good guides. Good team."

        Leafwhisper makes a sound like a pleased sigh and says — "We'll tell everyone about you! The human who walked through Territory One with excellent endurance and wonderful curiosity—"

        Rootwalker says gently — "Leafwhisper."

        Leafwhisper responds — "Right, yes, I'm talking too much again, it's just—it's been really nice! Having you with us. And I'll miss the questions, and Buddy's medical commentary, and Scout's enthusiastic investigations—"

        I step forward and, feeling slightly ridiculous but not caring, touch Leafwhisper's leaves gently. I say — "I'll miss your explanations. All of them. Even the really long ones about soil composition."

        Leafwhisper's leaves rustle with clear emotion. Leafwhisper says — "*Especially* those ones probably! Travel well, Kira Voss. Reach Elder Heartwood. Find your answers."

        Then I turn to Rootwalker. The tall root-structure stands solid and grounded as always.

        I say — "Thank you. For the water, and the quiet, and knowing when to say 'Time.'"

        Rootwalker makes a sound—deep, resonant. Then they do something unexpected.
